POLOKWANE – Mine workers are currently marching to the Anglo Platinum offices in Bendor to hand over a memorandum of grievances.  Miners from Polokwane, Sekhukhune and Mogalakwena first marched to the Department of Mineral Resources in Dorp Street where they demanded the department to intervene and urge Anglo Platinum Mining to treat their workers better. Miners are now on Potgieter Avenue headed to the Anglo Platinum office in Bendor to hand over a memorandum. Polokwane Observer journalist @Lizelle_becca is on the scene pic.twitter.com/oV26ISClIu — Polokwane Observer (@PolokwaneObserv) June 8, 2022  Motorists are urged to use alternative routes. Traffic officials are on the scene. 